column5: Beauty looking pike!!!...congrats!

Thanks for the comments. It hit in about 5 fow back trolling a black "Big Hammer" 5 inch swimbait on a 1 oz unpainted swimbait head.  It was the last day of an 11 day trip, and i hadn't landed a big fish yet, so she was very welcome to come have a rest in my cradle for a few minutes.  These big hammer swimbaits are amazing, They have a great balance of price,durability and action.  These things swim great even with the slowest retrieves.
nice fish.
Maybe it's just my eyes, but the colour and pattern of the head doesn't seem to match the rest of the fish.  Is that common with pike?
What a gorgeous fish, congrats on the PB.  Joey
The only appropriate response is WOW. What a beast, can't get over the head on her. Ducklings? Buh-bye. Ducks? Buh-bye. Moose? OK, maybe not just yet...
OMG! Nice one

nice fish  from what i've seen head size has more to do with environment and forage than whether a fish has potential to grow into anything  given the same length, fish that tend to spend most of their lives in deep water have smaller heads, shallow water fish the opposite.  great lakes (deep) fish that may eat a lot of alewife, cisco may have smaller heads than inland lake fish that spend time eating shallow water food
Yup, thats a nice Pike!
Just when you thought it was safe to go back in the water. An unbelievable creature....
Great fish. What a gorilla
Now we know how the rumors of Toe Monsters living in the water comes from. Nice fish   Art
Wow. Thats a gorgeous head, I mean Pike! Awesome looking fish man. Out of 5fow no less...
go it!
44 inch, guessing 30 lbs, based on a 46 i had on a scale that tipped 28.5.
Nice gator buddy!!!
Look at the head on that thing.  Nicely done.

This fish made me think...I mean will this fish actually grow into its head? It was unproportional to any fish i have caught before.  Ive seen 42's that are obviously genetically maxed out, they look in proportion. Then you get a 38 that has the head of a 42, and a body that seems that it cant catch up, In my opinion the 38 with the big melon has the potential to be a monster, while the in-proportion 42 is about as big as she's gonna get.  So if the moose( thats what i named her) actually grows into that noggin im thinkin g she'll be a 50+++ class fish
Just beautiful! Congrats to you.
What a beast..............I asked b4 but never checked again, what does PB stand for??
Great fish Really big head That shows she will get even bigger before she is done. Congrats
Personal Best and thats a nice PB gator just a big thick fish.

I was told that fish head size is based on age and growth rates. A fish with a large melon is an old slow growing fish. Smaller head would indicate a younger or faster growing fish. No matter what, that's a great fish you caught. Best of luck breaking that PB.
Big chunky pike, really nice !!  Been a very long time since that big girl was called a snot rocket.
That is awesome!
Man! Was that pike caught in Ontario? I used to dream about catching big pike and I barely recently broke the 10lb mark. That is definitely a fish of a lifetime! Thanks for sharing.
WOW, I would love to catch a Pike of that size! Unreal catch sir!  Thanks for sharing, MTBF
wow thats things beast, monstrous head on it! congrats definately a fish of a lifetime
HUGE fish.. please give us more detail on the catch..
Amazing catch!  It looks like his yap is big enough to eat your head, don't go swimming in that lake
That's a beauty!!
Awesome fish! Congrats!!
Beauty gator Congrats Leechman
I can see that thing taking on a 20lb Muskie any day, lol  Way to go man
Awesome fish and a great time of year to catch her.  I am sure it was a monster of a fight.
looks like a dragon compared to the pike i catch
Oy yoy!!!  beauty
Great looking pike, wow!
